# Next.js 16

> Your training data is almost certainly out of date for Next 16. Before writing any Next-specific code, consult `apps/web/node_modules/next/dist/docs/` and/or invoke the `next16-docs` subagent. See `.cursor/rules/docs-first.mdc`.

## App Router only

- Routes live under `apps/web/src/app/**`. Never create a `pages/` directory.
- No `getServerSideProps`, `getStaticProps`, `getInitialProps`, `_app.tsx`, `_document.tsx`. These do not exist here.
- Route Handlers live at `apps/web/src/app/**/route.ts` (not `api/*.ts` in a pages tree).
- Special files: `layout.tsx`, `page.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `template.tsx`, `default.tsx`, `route.ts`, `middleware.ts` (top level).

## Server vs client components

- **Server Components are the default.** Don't add `"use client"` unless you genuinely need hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs.
- `"use client"` marks a _boundary_, not a per-component attribute. Once a subtree is client, its children don't need their own directive.
- Do not put `"use client"` on leaf interactive components when a parent is already client.
- Server Components can be `async` and `await` data directly. Do this instead of a `useEffect + setState` dance.

## Async `params` and `searchParams`

In Next 15+ (and therefore 16), `params` and `searchParams` in page / layout / route handlers are **Promises**. You must `await` them:

```tsx
export default async function Page({
  params,
  searchParams,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ id: string }>;
  searchParams: Promise<Record<string, string | string[] | undefined>>;
}) {
  const { id } = await params;
  const query = await searchParams;
  // ...
}
```

Forgetting the `await` is the single most common Next-16-specific bug LLMs produce. Don't.

## Route handlers

```ts
// apps/web/src/app/games/[id]/route.ts
export async function GET(_request: Request, { params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }) {
  const { id } = await params;
  // ...
  return Response.json({ id });
}
```

- Export `GET`, `POST`, `PATCH`, `PUT`, `DELETE`, etc., as named async functions.
- Return `Response` or `Response.json()`. Do not import `NextResponse` unless you specifically need its features (rewrite/redirect/cookies helpers).

## Metadata

Use static `metadata` export or `generateMetadata` (async). Example in `apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx`. Metadata types come from `next`, not a sub-path.

## Fonts and images

- Fonts via `next/font/google` or `next/font/local`. Already wired in `layout.tsx` using Geist.
- Images via `next/image`. Any external host must be listed in `remotePatterns` inside `apps/web/next.config.ts`. Never hardcode dimensions — use `fill` with a sized parent or pass `width`/`height`.

## Next config

`apps/web/next.config.ts` has `transpilePackages: ['@gamevine/shared']` and `experimental.typedRoutes: true`. The typed routes feature means `Link` `href` is type-checked against actual route segments — don't work around it with `as any` or string casts.

## Caching

Next 16 caching semantics changed again. Never assume; look up `fetch` options, `revalidate`, `no-store`, `cache`, `unstable_cache`, `use cache`, and the route segment config in the docs before relying on them. Use `next16-docs` for questions.

## Middleware

One `apps/web/src/middleware.ts` per app. Export `middleware` and optional `config.matcher`. Runs on the Edge runtime by default — Node APIs are unavailable unless you opt in.

## Forbidden

- Creating `apps/web/pages/**`.
- Importing from `next/router` (it's `next/navigation`).
- `getServerSideProps` / `getStaticProps` / `getInitialProps`.
- Forgetting to `await` `params` or `searchParams`.
- Hardcoding an external image host without updating `remotePatterns`.
- Writing a client component that could be a Server Component.
